  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (107f477 2022-04-28T00:08:47.183276+00:00)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (amd)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\n- I have a contract inside the `contracts` dir that have a function that start with `test..()`\r\n- A solidity test file meant to be run by foundry inside `contracts/foundry-test/` dir\r\n- `test = 'contracts/foundry-test'` in foundry.toml\r\n\r\nWhen running `forge test` I expected that it should run the solidity files inside `contracts/foundry-test` only, but still it run the `test..()`.",
